 "summary_en": "The Moscone Center's record centers on building and expanding it. A 1991 environmental report notes the 1978 review analyzed the George R. Moscone Convention Center, which \"was opened on December 10, 1981,\" and a 1992 report describes voters approving the underground expansion of exhibit and meeting space. A 1988 Board of Supervisors journal logs ordinances financing the expansion, and 2001 Finance Committee minutes record a design agreement with Gensler amended to a total not exceeding $15,026,326, with floor area growing from 570,000 to 780,000 square feet. City permit data lists 145 permits totaling about $559 million declared, including a 2015 renovation declared at $266,061,486. It falls under the City Administrator, whose FY2025 budget line is $288M.",
